title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should display in data set dialog.
description: When calling a stored procedure from the Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, while on the query result page, no data is being returned and the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: While on the query result page, no data is being returned and the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog when on the query result page and there should be returned data.
SR: Steps to reproduce: 1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database. 2. Navigate to the query result page. Result: No data is returned and the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
